# Dictionary and word validation

Word validation is core gameplay. Regressions here break player trust.

## Before changing code

1. Read [`docs/validation_test_cases.md`](../../docs/validation_test_cases.md) for expected accept/reject behavior.
2. Understand normalization in `lib/dictionary/normalize.ts` and validation in `lib/dictionary/validate-word.ts`.

## After changing logic

1. Add or update tests in `tests/dictionary.test.ts` or related files.
2. Run dictionary regression cases (also run by `npm run ci:check`):

```bash
npm run dict:validate
```

3. If build pipeline or artifact layout changes, update `scripts/dictionary/README.md` and [`assets/README.md`](../../assets/README.md).

Do not change `assets/generated/dictionaries/` by hand — use `npm run dict:build` / `dict:all`.
